channel.title: Speculate wildly about Bioware's new game!
channel.description:
Gentlemen.
[url='https://kotaku.com/5692132/a-glimpse-at-biowares-next-game']https://kotaku.com/5692132/a-glimpse-at-biowares-next-game[/url] [quote] Bioware's official Twitter account, @Biofeed has put out two QR image codes. They are those image that you scan on your phone to pull up a specific App or bookmark or something.
Once they are fully scanned (takes a while) the images are large binary numbers. The two numbers have been: 55.845 and -128.5°F. [/quote]

item.title: Speculate wildly about Bioware's new game!
item.dc:creator: Orpheon
item.description:
DiePoente:

It looks like a military FPS for me

Hence the reason many believe its during the First Contact War of Mass Effect. The design of the soldier’s weapon and armor also lends some credence to the idea that it’s in that universe.

Some also think it could be a sequel to Shattered Steel, a 1996 mech game from Bioware, though I see no good evidence to support that yet.

item.title: Speculate wildly about Bioware's new game!
item.dc:creator: Orpheon
item.description:
rtanger:

This rumor angers me and intrigues me all at the same time…

Multiplayer? In MY Mass Effect?
shrugs
I dunno.

…i’m on the fence.

I think that explanation sounds pretty plausible. I don’t get why people are getting all mad about it though. If what Kotaku says is true, then it’ll just be a spin-off aimed at the shooter/multiplayer audience. Mass Effect 3 will probably not be influenced at all. Oh well. Can’t please everyone.
